I'm crazy like that... I like all the classes.  Except dr00d.  I would never play one of those mangy mutts.<br>
<br>
Twink up a tank, you'll level pretty quick and find lots of groups.  Low levels are fun!  Then go back to your wizard when you get bored.<br>
<br>
I play my alts until friends log in... I dont' really bother shouting for group with my wizard anymore, I wait for a guild event or something.<br>
<br>
Wizards sux0r!<br>
<br>
I love my wizard!<br>
<br>
I'm insane! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uobey555.showPublicProfile?language=EN>obey555</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/13/01 11:58:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> no, dont start another class..</span><hr size=1> I really disagree witht the argument that starting another class instanly fixes everything Verant did to the Wizard Class. First, it means you wasted all that time on a class that is now(45th?) useless to groups. Secondly, who really wants to dump their preferred class choice so they can play this game? No, I think its more logical to dump EQ than to start over, twink or not.<br>
My 2 cp. <br>
Soon.../rude Verant<br>
